  91:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****     [..]
  92:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      Use function @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_UnRegisterCallback to reset a callback to the default
  93:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      weak function.
  94:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
  95:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      and the Callback ID.
  96:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      This function allows to reset following callbacks:
  97:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) TxCpltCallback           : callback for Tx Completed.
  98:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) RxCpltCallback           : callback for Rx Completed.
  99:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) PreambleDetectedCallback : callback for Preamble detected.
 100:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) SyncWordValidCallback    : callback for Synchro word valid.
 101:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) HeaderValidCallback      : callback for Header valid.
 102:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) HeaderErrorCallback      : callback for Header error.
 103:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) CRCErrorCallback         : callback for CRC Error.
 104:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) RxTxTimeoutCallback      : callback for Rx Tx Timeout.
 105:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) MspInitCallback          : callback for Msp Init.
 106:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) MspDeInitCallback        : callback for Msp DeInit.
 107:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****        (+) LrFhssHopCallback        : callback for LoRa Frequency Hopping Spread Spectrum Hopping.
 108:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****     [..]
 109:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      For specific callback CADStatusCallback use dedicated register callbacks :
 110:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_UnRegisterCadStatusCallback().
 111:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****     [..]
 112:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      MspInit and MspDeInit functions are reset to the legacy weak functions in the
 113:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_Init()/ @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null
 114:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      (not registered beforehand).
 115:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      If MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_Init()/ @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_DeInit()
 116:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand) whatever the state.
 117:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c **** 
 118:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****     [..]
 119:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      Callbacks for MspInit/MspDeInit functions can be registered/unregistered
 120:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      in @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_STATE_READY or @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_STATE_RESET state,
 121:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 122:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      Then, the user first registers the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 123:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      using @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_RegisterCallback() before calling @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_DeInit()
 124:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      or @ref HAL_SUBGHZ_Init() function.
 125:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c **** 
 126:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****     [..]
 127:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      When the compilation flag USE_HAL_SUBGHZ_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 128:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
 129:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c ****      are set to the corresponding weak functions.
 130:Drivers/STM32WLxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wlxx_hal_subghz.c **** #endif
